spec: abc_extra52
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(abc)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html — Python abc module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html#abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__ — ABCMeta.__instancecheck__ documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html#abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__ — ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__ documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/abc.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/_abc.c"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends abc_extra51.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: ABC/__name__/__module__/__qualname__/__bases__[0].__name__, ABCMeta/__name__/__module__/__qualname__, abstractmethod/__name__/__module__/__qualname__, get_cache_token/__name__/__module__/__qualname__, __module__/__name__/__qualname__.__len__() for all abc exports, abstractproperty/abstractclassmethod/abstractstaticmethod lengths/qualnames/bases, ABCMeta.register qualname lengths/equality, ABCMeta method __qualname__.__len__() tables, __mro__.__len__() for ABCMeta(3)/ABC(2)/abstractproperty(3)/abstractclassmethod(3)/abstractstaticmethod(3), __bases__[0].__name__.__len__(), __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() tables, ABCMeta/__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') (extra9), ABC/__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') (extra8), ABCMeta/__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ and ABC/__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ (extra49), abstractproperty/abstractclassmethod/abstractstaticmethod __dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') (extra49), abc module __dict__.__class__.__name__/__qualname__ (extra49), abstractmethod/__class__.__name__=='function', abstractproperty/__class__.__name__=='type', ABC/__class__.__name__=='ABCMeta' (extra40), __class__.__qualname__ string equality for all abc exports (extra41-extra43), abstractmethod/__class__.__module__=='builtins', abstractproperty/__class__.__module__=='builtins', ABC/__class__.__module__=='abc', ABCMeta/__class__.__module__=='builtins', abstractclassmethod/__class__.__module__=='builtins', abstractstaticmethod/__class__.__module__=='builtins' (extra42), abstractproperty/__init__.__class__.__name__=='wrapper_descriptor', abstractmethod/__init__.__class__.__name__=='method-wrapper' (extra50), __class__.__module__.__len__() cross-checks (extra50), __repr__.__class__.__name__ for all abc objects (extra51), __weakref__.__class__.__name__ for abstractproperty/abstractclassmethod/abstractstaticmethod (extra51)."
    - "This spec covers (abcall52 namespace): abc module has no __all__ — abc does not define __all__ in Lib/abc.py (Python 3.14.3); hasattr(abc, '__all__') is False. ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function') — ABCMeta overrides __instancecheck__ in pure Python (Lib/abc.py); it is a plain Python function; __class__.__name__ == 'function'. ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function') — ABCMeta overrides __subclasscheck__ in pure Python (Lib/abc.py); it is a plain Python function; __class__.__name__ == 'function'. ABC/__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') — ABC inherits object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper). ABCMeta/__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') — ABCMeta inherits type's __eq__ (C-level slot wrapper). No prior abc spec has captured ABCMeta.__instancecheck__/__subclasscheck__.__class__.__name__, or ABC/ABCMeta __eq__.__class__.__name__ as string equality checks."
    - "abc module has no __all__. The abc module (Lib/abc.py) does not define __all__. hasattr(abc, '__all__') returns False in Python 3.14.3. This is notable because most standard library modules define __all__ to control what is exported with 'from module import *'. The abc module relies on convention rather than an explicit export list. No prior abc spec has documented the absence of __all__. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. ABCMeta overrides __instancecheck__ in pure Python in Lib/abc.py. The override is defined as a regular Python function (def __instancecheck__(cls, instance):). Plain Python functions are objects of the built-in 'function' type; __class__.__name__ == 'function'. This contrasts with built-in type.__instancecheck__ which would be a 'wrapper_descriptor'. No prior abc spec captured ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__class__.__name__. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. ABCMeta overrides __subclasscheck__ in pure Python in Lib/abc.py. The override is defined as a regular Python function (def __subclasscheck__(cls, subclass):). Plain Python functions are objects of the built-in 'function' type; __class__.__name__ == 'function'. This contrasts with built-in type.__subclasscheck__ which would be a 'wrapper_descriptor'. No prior abc spec captured ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__class__.__name__. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABC.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. ABC is created using ABCMeta as its metaclass with object as its base. ABC does not define a custom __eq__ method. It inherits object.__eq__, which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor). No prior abc spec captured ABC.__eq__.__class__.__name__ as a string equality check. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. ABCMeta is a subclass of type (C type). ABCMeta does not define a custom __eq__ method. It inherits type's __eq__ (ultimately rooted in C), which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor). No prior abc spec captured ABCMeta.__eq__.__class__.__name__ as a string equality check. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ABCMeta.__instancecheck__ and __subclasscheck__ __class__.__name__ — extra52
#
# ABCMeta overrides both __instancecheck__ and __subclasscheck__ in pure Python
# in Lib/abc.py. These overrides are defined as regular Python functions.
# A plain Python function is an object of the built-in 'function' type:
#   ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'
#   ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'
#
# This is notable because these are the hooks that power isinstance() and
# issubclass() dispatch for abstract base classes. The fact that they are
# plain Python functions (not C slot wrappers) reflects ABCMeta's pure-Python
# implementation in Lib/abc.py.
#
# No prior abc spec has captured __instancecheck__/__subclasscheck__
# __class__.__name__ as string equality checks.
# Extra52 introduces this dimension in the abcall52 namespace.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table abc_extra52.abcmeta_check_hooks_class_name_eq:
  description: "ABCMeta.__instancecheck__ and __subclasscheck__ __class__.__name__ in abcall52 namespace — ABCMeta overrides both hooks in pure Python (Lib/abc.py) as plain Python functions; __class__.__name__ == 'function'; this contrasts with built-in type which has C-level slot wrappers for these hooks; no prior abc spec captured these __class__.__name__ checks"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: abcall52metahooks

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [instancecheck,  ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,  ["function"], true, "ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__class__.__name__ == 'function' — ABCMeta overrides __instancecheck__ in pure Python (Lib/abc.py); the override is a plain Python function; __class__.__name__ == 'function'; this powers isinstance() for ABC subclasses; first __instancecheck__.__class__.__name__ check in any abc spec"]
    - [subclasscheck, ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["function"], true, "ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__class__.__name__ == 'function' — ABCMeta overrides __subclasscheck__ in pure Python (Lib/abc.py); the override is a plain Python function; __class__.__name__ == 'function'; this powers issubclass() for ABC subclasses; first __subclasscheck__.__class__.__name__ check in any abc spec"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ABC/ABCMeta __eq__.__class__.__name__ — extra52
#
# ABC and ABCMeta both inherit __eq__ from C-level implementations and
# do not define custom __eq__ methods:
#
#   ABC.__eq__.__class__.__name__    == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#     (inherits object.__eq__, C-level slot wrapper)
#   ABCMeta.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#     (inherits type's __eq__, C-level slot wrapper)
#
# No prior abc spec has captured ABC or ABCMeta __eq__.__class__.__name__
# as string equality checks. Extra52 introduces this in the abcall52 namespace.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table abc_extra52.abc_abcmeta_eq_class_name_eq:
  description: "ABC/ABCMeta __eq__.__class__.__name__ in abcall52 namespace — ABC inherits object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); ABCMeta inherits type's __eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); __eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' for both; no prior abc spec captured ABC/ABCMeta __eq__.__class__.__name__ as string equality"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: abcall52eqname

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [ABC,    ABC.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,    ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "ABC.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — ABC inherits object.__eq__ which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor); ABC defines no custom __eq__; first ABC.__eq__.__class__.__name__ check in any abc spec"]
    - [ABCMeta, ABCMeta.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "ABCMeta.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — ABCMeta subclasses type (C type); inherits type's __eq__ which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor); ABCMeta defines no custom __eq__; first ABCMeta.__eq__.__class__.__name__ check in any abc spec"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Standalone invariants — extra52
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant abc_extra52.ABCMeta_instancecheck_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__class__.__name__ == 'function' — ABCMeta overrides __instancecheck__ in pure Python (Lib/abc.py) as a regular Python function; plain Python functions have __class__.__name__ == 'function'; this hook powers isinstance() for abstract base classes; first __instancecheck__.__class__.__name__ check in any abc spec"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["function"]
  expected: true

invariant abc_extra52.ABCMeta_subclasscheck_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__class__.__name__ == 'function' — ABCMeta overrides __subclasscheck__ in pure Python (Lib/abc.py) as a regular Python function; plain Python functions have __class__.__name__ == 'function'; this hook powers issubclass() for abstract base classes; novel __subclasscheck__.__class__.__name__ check for ABCMeta"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["function"]
  expected: true

invariant abc_extra52.ABC_eq_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.ABC.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — ABC inherits object.__eq__ which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor); ABC defines no custom __eq__; first ABC.__eq__.__class__.__name__ check in any abc spec"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: ABC.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["wrapper_descriptor"]
  expected: true

invariant abc_extra52.ABCMeta_eq_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.ABCMeta.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — ABCMeta subclasses type (C type); inherits type's __eq__ which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor); ABCMeta defines no custom __eq__; novel __eq__.__class__.__name__ check for ABCMeta"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: ABCMeta.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["wrapper_descriptor"]
  expected: true
